objects.name: cyclops blink
objects.description: A malicious Linux ELF executable, compiled for the 32-bit PowerPC (big-endian) architecture, targeting SOHO network devices.

objects.name: FBI
objects.description: An organization that provided samples of Cyclops Blink for analysis.

objects.name: CISA
objects.description: An organization involved in the analysis of Cyclops Blink.

objects.name: NSA
objects.description: An organization involved in the analysis of Cyclops Blink.

objects.name: WatchGuard
objects.description: A company whose devices are targeted by Cyclops Blink.

objects.name: T1059.004
objects.description: Persistence: Cyclops Blink executes downloaded files using the Linux API function execlp.

objects.name: T1037.004
objects.description: Command and Scripting Interpreter: Unix Shell: Cyclops Blink uses the Linux API function execlp to execute files.

objects.name: T1542.001
objects.description: Pre-OS Boot: System Firmware: Cyclops Blink maintains persistence throughout the legitimate device firmware update process.

objects.name: T1562.004
objects.description: Impair Defenses: Disable or Modify System Firewall: Cyclops Blink modifies the Linux iptables firewall to enable C2 communication.

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Masquerading: Match Legitimate Name or Location: Cyclops Blink renames its running process to masquerade as a Linux kernel thread.

objects.name: T1082
objects.description: System Information Discovery: Cyclops Blink regularly queries device information.

objects.name: T1132.002
objects.description: Data Encoding: Non-Standard Encoding: Cyclops Blink command messages use a custom binary scheme to encode the specific command to be executed.

objects.name: T1008
objects.description: Fallback Channels: Cyclops Blink randomly selects a C2 server from contained lists of IPv4 addresses and port numbers.

objects.name: T1071.001
objects.description: Application Layer Protocol: Web Protocols: Cyclops Blink can download files via HTTP or HTTPS.

objects.name: T1573.002
objects.description: Encrypted Channel: Asymmetric Cryptography: Cyclops Blink C2 messages are individually encrypted using AES-256-CBC and sent underneath TLS.

objects.name: T1571
objects.description: Non-Standard Port: Cyclops Blink contains a list of port numbers used for C2 communication, including non-standard ports.

objects.name: T1041
objects.description: Exfiltration Over C2 Channel: Cyclops Blink is capable of uploading files to a C2 server.

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_notable_strings
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_notable_strings { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects notable strings identified within the Cyclops Blink executable" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $proc_name1 = "[kworker/0:1]" $proc_name2 = "[kworker/1:1]" $dns_query = "POST /dns-query HTTP/1.1\x0d\x0aHost: dns.google\x0d\x0a" $iptables1 = "iptables -I %s -p tcp --dport %d -j ACCEPT &>/dev/null" $iptables2 = "iptables -D %s -p tcp --dport %d -j ACCEPT &>/dev/null" $sys_recon1 = "{\"ver\":\"%x\",\"mods\";[" $sys_recon2 = "uptime: %lu mem_size: %lu mem_free: %lu" $sys_recon3 = "disk_size: %lu disk_free: %lu" $sys_recon4 = "hw: %02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x:%02x" $testpath = "%s/214688dsf46" $confpath = "%s/rootfs_cfg" $downpath = "/var/tmp/a.tmp" condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (8 of them) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_module_initialisation
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_module_initialisation { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the code bytes used to initialise the modules built into Cyclops Blink" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $ = {94 21 FF F0 93 E1 00 08 7C 3F 0B 78 38 00 00 ?? 7C 03 03 78 81 61 00 00 8E EB FF F8 7D 61 5B 78 4E 80 00 20} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (any of them) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_modified_install_upgrade
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_modified_install_upgrade { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects notable strings identified within the modified install_upgrade executable, embedded within Cyclops Blink" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" hash3 = "7d61c0dd0cd901221a9dff9df09bb90810754f10" hash4 = "438cd40caca70cafe5ca436b36ef7d3a6321e858" strings: $ = "/pending/%010lu_%06d_%03d_p1" $ = "/pending/sysa_code_dir/test_%d_%d_%d_%d_%d_%d" $ = "etaonrishdlcupfm" $ = "/pending/WGUpgrade-dl.new" $ = "/pending/bin/install_upgraded" $ = {38 80 4C 00} $ = {38 80 4C 05} $ = {38 80 4C 04} $ = {3C 00 48 4D 60 00 41 43 90 09 00 00} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (6 of them) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_core_command_check
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_core_command_check { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the code bytes used to test the command ID being sent to the core component of Cyclops Blink" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $cmd_check = {81 3F 00 18 88 09 00 05 54 00 06 3E 2F 80 00 00 (07|0A|0B|0C|0D)} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (#cmd_check == 5) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_config_identifiers
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_config_identifiers { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the initial characters used to identify Cyclops Blink configuration data" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $ = "<p: " fullword $ = {3C 00 3C 6B 60 00 3A 20 90 09 00 00} $ = {3C 00 3C 63 60 00 3A 20 90 09 00 00} $ = {3C 00 3C 73 60 00 3A 20 90 09 00 00} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (all of them) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_handle_mod_0xf_command
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_handle_mod_0xf_command { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the code bytes used to check module ID 0xf control flags and a format string used for file content upload" date = "2022-10-27" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $test_exec = {54 00 06 3E 54 00 07 FE 54 00 06 3E 2F 80 00 00} $test_addmod = {54 00 06 3E 54 00 07 BC 2F 80 00 00} $test_sc = {54 00 06 3E 54 00 07 7A 2F 80 00 00} $test_upload = {54 00 06 3E 54 00 06 F6 2F 80 00 00} $upload_fmt = "file:%s\n" fullword condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and ($upload_fmt) and ( for all i in (math.max(#test_exec, math.max(#test_addmod, math.max(#test_sc, #test_upload)))) : ( (@test_exec[math.min(i, #test_exec)] > @test_addmod[math.min(i, #test_addmod)]) and (@test_addmod[math.min(i, #test_addmod)] > @test_sc[math.min(i, #test_sc)]) and (@test_sc[math.min(i, #test_sc)] > @test_upload[math.min(i, #test_upload)]) and ((@test_exec[math.min(i, #test_exec)] - @test_upload[math.min(i, #test_upload)]) <= 0x180) ) ) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_default_config_values
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_default_config_values { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the code bytes used to set default Cyclops Blink configuration values" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $ = {38 00 00 19 90 09 01 A4} $ = {3C 00 00 01 60 00 80 00 90 09 01 A8} $ = {38 00 40 00 90 09 01 AC} $ = {38 00 01 0B 90 09 01 B0} $ = {38 00 27 11 90 09 01 C0} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (3 of them) }

objects.name: CyclopsBlink_handle_mod_0x51_command
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CyclopsBlink_handle_mod_0x51_command { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the code bytes used to check commands sent to module ID 0x51 and notable strings relating to the Cyclops Blink update process" date = "2022-02-23" hash1 = "3adf9a59743bc5d8399f67cab5eb2daf28b9b863" hash2 = "c59bc17659daca1b1ce65b6af077f86a648ad8a8" strings: $cmd_check = {88 1F [2] 54 00 06 3E 2F 80 00 (01|02|03)} $path1 = "/etc/wg/configd-hash.xml" $path2 = "/etc/wg/config.xml" $mnt_arg1 = "ext2" $mnt_arg2 = "errors=continue" $mnt_arg3 = {38 C0 0C 20} $mnt_arg4 = {38 C0 0C 21} condition: (uint32(0) == 0x464c457f) and (#cmd_check == 3) and ((@cmd_check[3] - @cmd_check[1]) < 0x200) and (all of ($path*)) and (all of ($mnt_arg*)) }
